## Installation

Installation is straightforward. The WallPod includes built-in PME fault detection (TruePEN technology), meaning **no earth rod is required**. This is a significant practical advantage:

- **Neater finish** — no metal rod sticking out of your garden
- **Less disruption** — no digging or drilling into the ground
- **Potentially lower installation cost** — simpler job for the electrician

The charger also includes built-in overcurrent protection and 6mA DC leakage detection, complying with current UK regulations without additional external protection devices.

Rolec has a network of approved installers across the UK, though it's not as extensive as Ohme's or myenergi's. You can also use any qualified electrician familiar with EV charger installations.

The WallPod is **OZEV grant eligible**. The EV Chargepoint Grant covers up to £350 towards installation for eligible renters, flat owners, and landlords. See our [OZEV grant guide](/guides/ev-charger-government-grant-uk/) for details.

After the OZEV grant (if eligible), you could be looking at £450–£650 all-in. That's genuinely hard to beat for a charger this feature-rich.

## Charging Speed

The WallPod delivers up to 7.4kW on a single-phase supply at 32A — matching the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) and [Hypervolt Home 3 Pro](/reviews/hypervolt-home-3-review/). That gives you approximately 28–30 miles of range per hour, with most EVs charging fully in 6–10 hours overnight.

A 3.6kW version is also available for properties with limited electrical capacity.

