## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is the Rolec WallPod compatible with Intelligent Octopus Go?

Not directly. The WallPod uses the ev.energy app for smart charging, which supports manual scheduling to align with off-peak tariffs like Octopus Go. However, it doesn't have the deep two-way integration with Intelligent Octopus Go that chargers like the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) or [Hypervolt Home 3 Pro](/reviews/hypervolt-home-3-review/) offer. For fixed off-peak windows (like standard Octopus Go), manual scheduling works fine. For dynamic slots (Intelligent Octopus Go), you lose some automatic flexibility.

### Is the Rolec WallPod a good budget EV charger?

Yes — it's one of the best-value home EV chargers available in the UK. For the price, you get features like dynamic load balancing (with included CT clamp), triple connectivity, RFID, MID metering, and OCPP compliance. These are features typically found on more expensive chargers. The main trade-off is the dated, industrial design.

### Does the Rolec WallPod need an earth rod?

No. The WallPod includes built-in TruePEN PME fault detection, eliminating the need for a separate earth rod. This makes installation quicker, neater, and often cheaper.

### Can I use the Rolec WallPod with solar panels?

Yes. Solar compatibility is available through the ev.energy app, which can detect surplus solar generation and prioritise charging from that energy. It's app-based rather than hardware-level (like the [myenergi Zappi](/reviews/zappi-v2-review/)), but it covers the basics. The WallPod also supports battery storage and wind turbine integration.

### How does the Rolec WallPod compare to the Ohme ePod?

Both sit in the budget bracket. The Ohme ePod has the edge on smart tariff integration (native Intelligent Octopus Go support) and design. The Rolec WallPod offers more hardware features: RFID, MID metering, OCPP compliance, triple connectivity, and dynamic load balancing with included CT clamp. The best choice depends on whether smart tariff savings or hardware features matter more to you.

